==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flanch
<hw>Flanch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Flanches</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Prov. E., a projection,
OF. <ets>flanche</ets> flank. See <er>Flank</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A flange.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>. <def2><fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>A
bearing consisting of a segment of a circle encroaching on the field
from the side.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Flanches</xex> are always in pairs. A pair of
<xex>flanches</xex> is considered one of the subordinaries.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flanched</ent>⟦br⟧
